<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Hesperocyparis</i> <i>abramsiana</i>, <i>Hesperocyparis</i> <i>goveniana</i>, <i>Hesperocyparis</i> <i>macrocarpa</i> and/or <i>Hesperocyparis</i> <i>pigmaea</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the tree canopy with <i>Arbutus</i> <i>menziesii</i>, <i>Pinus</i> <i>attenuata</i>, <i>Pinus</i> <i>muricata</i>, <i>Pinus</i> <i>radiata</i>, <i>Pseudotsuga</i> <i>menziesii</i>, <i>Quercus</i> <i>agrifolia</i> and <i>Sequoia</i> <i>sempervirens</i>. Shrubs may include <i>Adenostoma</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>andersonii</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>columbiana</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>crustacea</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>hookeri</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>nummularia</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>sensitiva</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>silvicola</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>tomentosa</i>, <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>cuneatus</i> var. <i>rigidus</i>, <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>thyrsiflorus</i>, <i>Rhododendron</i> <i>macrophyllum</i> or <i>Vaccinium</i> <i>ovatum</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text"> Trees < 2 m or 15 m (depending on site conditions); canopy is open to continuous. Shrub layer is open to continuous. Herbaceous layer is sparse. Lichens and mosses occur on the soil surface and on the woody plants as epiphytes. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Hesperocyparis pigmaea</i> > 30% relative cover in the tree canopy (VegCAMP 2019).</li>
		
		<li><i>Hesperocyparis pigmaea</i> dominates the tree canopy (Westman 1975).</li>
		
		<li><i>Hesperocyparis abramsiana</i> > 30% relative cover in the tree canopy (Sikes et al. 2021).</li>
		
		<li>Stands > 50% relative cover of endemic tree taxa <i>Hesperocyparis macrocarpa, H. goveniana</i>, and/or <i>H. abramsiana</i> that occur in scattered groves along the coast (NatureServe 2021)</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Uplifted marine terraces, sandstone, and granitic outcrops. Soils are often acidic spodosols with hardpans or nutrient-deficient soils; some sites are seasonally flooded.  </div>
</div>

        
